{"questionId":"22705579","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Similarly, it can be shown that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>Y</mi><mo>.</mo></mover><mo>≈</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>X</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Given that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mover><mi>X</mi><mo>.</mo></mover></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mover><mi>Y</mi><mo>.</mo></mover></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">M</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mi>X</mi></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi>Y</mi></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">M</mi></math>&nbsp;is a square matrix, write down <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">M</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"bold-italic\">M</mi><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd><mtd><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>4</mn></mtd><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22705579","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ2.2f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Given that X.Y.=MXY, where M is a square matrix, write down M.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.15—Eigenvalues and eigenvectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}